Diagnosis
: Recognized by the relatively small size (
13.1–15.7 mm
), black body, lack of pale margin on the scutellum, dark red legs, red corium (
Fig. 1H
), posterior margin of the dorsal phallothecal sclerite rounded in dorsal view, and dorsolateral lobes divided into proximal and distal portions, both portions short and tongue shaped.

Female: Total length 
13.69–15.65 mm
. STRUCTURE: ABDOMEN: syntergite 9/10 with distal margin flat (
Fig. 11 H
). GENITALIA: gonapophysis 8 with two distinct sclerotizations (
Fig. 15H
), bursa copulatrix with two narrow, transverse sclerotized folds (
Fig. 14H
).
